Hundreds of shell casings and shot cars: showing the consequences of a shootout in Ingushetia In Karabulak, the cordon was lifted in the courtyard where a shootout took place between FSB special forces and liquidated IS terrorists*, reports Izvestia correspondent Murad Magomedov.

There were bullet marks on the buildings. Parked cars turned into a sieve. Several apartments on the third and fourth floors of the building were destroyed, and smoke is still coming from the windows of one of them, the correspondent noted. Investigators are working along the entire perimeter. What is known about the counter-terrorism operation in Ingushetia: At night, militants barricaded themselves in an apartment building and responded to an offer to surrender with shooting. They were armed with a large number of automatic weapons and explosive devices; The terrorists attempted to escape using a rope from the window, but they failed; Special forces of the Russian FSB eliminated six terrorists - followers of ISIS *, a source told Izvestia. Weapons, ammunition and IEDs were found at the site of the clash;

According to our sources, the neutralization of the bandits was the result of large-scale work by operational services, which uncovered the activities of a terrorist underground coordinated from abroad.* - Recognized as terrorist in the Russian Federation, the activity is prohibitedSubscribe to REN TV

